The best way is to use XSLT-1.0 to transform your input XML to your desired output XML.  
This can be achieved by using [`XslCompiledTransform`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.xml.xsl.xslcompiledtransform?view=netframework-4.8).  
The following stylesheet (`transform.xslt`) does the job:

    &lt;xsl:stylesheet version=&quot;1.0&quot; xmlns:xsl=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform&quot;&gt;
    
        &lt;!-- Identity template --&gt; 
        &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;node()|@*&quot;&gt;
            &lt;xsl:copy&gt;
                &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;node()|@*&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;
