Yes, ts converts `[string, number]` into `(string | number)[]` unless you explicitly specify type of each item:

```typescript
combineLatest([of(1), of(&#39;test&#39;)]).pipe(
    map(([myNumber, myString]) =&gt; {
        return [myNumber, myString] as [number, string];
    }),
    map(([myNewNumber, myNewString]) =&gt; {
        const test = myNewString.length;
    }),
);
```

Or you can use Object instead of Array if you don&#39;t want to deal with explicit types:

```typescript
combineLatest([of(1), of(&#39;test&#39;)]).pipe(
    map(([myNumber, myString]) =&gt; {
        return {myNumber, myString};
    }),
    map(({myNewNumber, myNewString}) =&gt; {
        const test = myNewString.length;
    })
);
```

